post_text:
We would like to express our appreciation for the success of the alternative meal program during the COVID-19 crisis to the following groups:

Our generous donators,

·Rose Acres for donating 300 dozen eggs, which allowed us to distribute a dozen eggs to each family for 3 weeks.

·Aldi Foods for donating grocery bags, which allowed for each child to have their own sack on distribution days.

·Ruler Foods for donating loaves of bread to include with the meals.

·Healthy Communities for the many household items that were passed out to the families.

We would also like to thank the parents who signed up their children and picked up their meals. We would like to thank Mr. Remaly for all his help and support in the planning and all the hours he spent helping with our distribution of the meals. We would like to thank our Administration for helping pass out the meals. We also acknowledge our fellow co-workers who worked hard together and with combined efforts in the Elementary to prepare and pass out the meals.

Sincerely,
Becky McQuinn and Tina Crum

Completed physical packets that were in use for the 2019-20 school year (for grades 5-11) will be permitted - by the IHSAA and the Committee on Sports Medicine at the Indiana State Medical Association - for use during the 2020-21 school year, ONLY if a physical packet is currently on file in the Athletic Office. Updated physical packets for the 2020-21 school year will soon be available in the Athletic Office and on the school website.

post_text:
Good morning seniors. Josten's will be at school next Tuesday, April 14 from 10:00am to noon for a drive-by senior supply (cap/gown) pickup.

We will have tables set up under the canopy on the north side of the high school. You will drive through and pay for and pick up your supplies.

Josten's sent you an invoice last month on what or if you owe a balance. If you still have a balance due, please bring CASH or MONEY ORDER to the pickup.

This is the only pickup we have scheduled. Please make arrangements to pick up your supplies.

If you can't find your Josten's invoice -- and don't know your balance -- please send me an email and I will contact Josten's for you.

A date for graduation has not been confirmed -- but I do know that Mr. Remaly and Mr. Smith are working to make sure you have a graduation ceremony. If you ordered announcements in your senior supply -- you will also receive change of date cards at no extra charge.

If you have any other questions -- please let me know.

Mrs. Runyon

post_text:
The Governor announced today that schools will remain closed for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. If you have been following the news, this should not come as a big surprise but it is definitely the right thing to do.

Our new normal of e learning will continue under the current format for the remainder of the year. Clinton Central will also continue to use the waiver days allowed and in the next couple of days, we will be sending out a calendar for the remainder of the year. We know there will be questions about graduation, credits, being promoted to the next grade, etc… Once the administration knows all of the specifics, we will communicate them to you.

We greatly appreciate all your efforts at home, remember we are all in this together.

Please remember that the 21st Century Scholar Deadline is approaching. You can enroll your child as a 21st Century Scholar from the time they enter 7th grade to June 30th of their 8th grade year.

This is a wonderful opportunity to have the majority of college expenses paid for. Please take advantage of this opportunity.

The following is the link to the enrollment page: https://learnmoreindiana.org/scholars/enroll/

post_text:
Hi seniors -- I know this is supposed to be an exciting time -- getting ready to graduate -- instead you are quarantined at home, trying to stay healthy.

We know you've worked very hard for this moment. But as you all know -- everything is on hold for at least the month of April.

Unfortunately, that means the cap and gown pickup that was scheduled for this Tuesday. March 31 is cancelled.

At this point, a new date for pickup has not been scheduled.

If you have any questions about graduation please feel free to contact any of us, we will try to answer your questions.

Mr. Smith
Mrs. Dunn
Mrs. Eli
Mrs. Runyon

post_text:
Bulldog Families,

We are pleased to announce that our awesome cafeteria staff will once again be putting together Breakfast and Lunches for our Clinton Central students and siblings (Infant - 12th grade).

Pick up will be Monday, March 30th and Wednesday, April 1st from 4:30pm - 6pm, in the Elementary Cafeteria. (Located on the Northside of the Elementary - doors N7 & N8)

You MUST PRE-ORDER by NOON March 30th for both pickups!!!! (Even if you only want April 1st meals)
Monday's pick up will contain 2 days of food - Wednesday's pick up will contain 3 days of food

Call Becky McQuinn - 765-249-0202 or email - becky.mcquinn@clinton.k12.in.us
or Tina Crum - 765-249-2244 ext 3376 or email - tina.crum@clinton.k12.in.us

School Supplies are available too for pick up during this time!

We hope you are all staying safe and we wish you all good health.

Clinton Central School Corporation

Clinton Central Food Services will be providing free food to Clinton Central students, as well as any child in the district, ages infant through 18 years old. This includes breakfast and lunch meals.

Food will be distributed today, Wednesday, March 18th from 4:30 pm to 6:00pm and it will need to be PICKED UP at Door N7 or N8 at Clinton Central Elementary.

Food must be pre-ordered by calling or emailing no later than Wednesday, March 18th at 12 noon.

You may call at 249-0202 or email becky.mcquinn@clinton.k12.in.us

In addition to food pick up, we have a limited amount of school supplies available that your student may need to complete e-learning assignments. A table will be set up for these supplies to be picked up in the cafeteria during the food distribution times.

post_text:
Clinton Central will be closed today, February 13th and will be e-learning!

Students,

The following must be completed in order to be counted present for today’s E-Learning:

1) Go to the Clinton Central webpage
2) On the top right of the webpage, you will see a link/tab that says "For Student." Navigate your cursor over the top of it and a drop down menu will offer you a link that is titled E-Learning. Please select it.
3) Once you are on the E-Learning page, be sure to fill in your first name, last name, email address, lunch ID, click present, enter the verification code and then click submit.

If you do not complete this process, you will be counted absent. If you have any issue with the E-Learning page, please contact Mr. Pfahl via email.

SUPPORT BULLDOG ATHLETICS!

It's not to late to show your Bulldog pride and join the Clinton Central Athletic Booster Club for the 2019-2020 school year! Get your membership form and money in by November 15th and your name will be listed in the winter sports program. The Booster Club provides scholarships, funding for letter jackets, support for athletic signage & equipment, publishes the fall, winter and spring sports programs and promotes school spirit.

post_text: Due to the weather forecast for Friday night, the decision has been made to move the chili cook off to next Friday evening. We will keep our fingers crossed that next Friday will work. If it rains next Friday we will move it to the MPR. It should be a fun evening next week. It is Halloween costume night, the Chili cook off and senior night. Please help us cheer on our Bulldogs and submit your chili during the tailgate next Friday for the last home game. Thanks for your understanding...please spread the word!

It's Homecoming Week! Below is our list of activities for the week. Go Bulldogs!!!

Monday
Dress Up Day: Country VS Country Club
Activity: Hallway Decorating @ 5pm

Tuesday
Dress Up Day: Twin Day
Activity: Boy's Volleyball following Varsity Girls Game

Wednesday
Dress Up Day: Mathletes VS Athletes
Activity: Powderpuff Game- Warm up @ 6pm by football field, Game starts @ 6:30. Halftime show with Senior Boys Football!

Thursday
Dress Up Day: Class Shirts
Activity: King Crowning between JV and Varsity Game. Bonfire after game until 10:30

Friday
Dress Up Day: Vsco Girl
Activity: Reverse Two-Hour Delay Schedule in the afternoon starting at 1pm.
There will be a pep session, a float parade, and trike races from 1-3. More info will be given during PD Tuesday regarding Friday's events.
Queen Crowning during halftime of the Varsity game.
